      "text": "Future or no future - is it worth arguing about? Everyone will refer to his knowledge of the world, will report first-hand, as it were, will describe what he can observe. Therefore, it may be advisable to move from \"what-questions\" to \"how-questions\". This brings one into a perspective of second-order observation, the observation of observers. And the question is no longer what is in front of us, but how is described what is in front of us. The interest turns to the form of descriptions of the future."
